    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"necessary investment\" sounds a bit optimistic. some of the local guys i talk to are saying the costs are just gonna kill their margins and they can't actually innovate their way out of it. do you have any data on whether the \"innovation\" part actually happens for small shops, or is that just a theoretical thing?",
